{"lemma":"مَسَدُ","slug":"مَسَدُ","root":"م.س.د","root_slug":"م-س-د","root_link":"/words/roots/م-س-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَسَد","root":"مسد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":10,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":15},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38587","n38588","n19297","n19298"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fibres from the frond of the palm tree","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ropes processed thereof","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shaft (of a pulley)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to twist tightly, to plait (a rope, etc.)","tags":["collective","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of مَسَدَ (masada, “to twist tightly, to plait”) (form I)","tags":["collective","form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to accelerate, to hasten","tags":["collective","intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to weaken","tags":["collective","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tone (the body or stomach), to make strong and with firm skin","tags":["collective","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become toned (of the body or a body part, especially the stomach)","tags":["collective","intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rub gently with one's hand, to massage, to caress","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"بَدَأْتُ أُمَسِّدُ شَعْرَهَا. سَأُغَسِّلُهَا بِالمَطَر! اِبْتَسَمَتْ كَأَنَّهَا سَمَعَتْ مَا فَكَرْتُ بِه.","english":"I began to caress her hair. I’ll clean her with rainwater! She smiled as if she heard what I was thinking about."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of مَسَدَ (masada, “to hasten; to weaken; to make toned”) (form I)","tags":["collective","form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of أَسْدَى (ʔasdā)","tags":["active","collective","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of أَسَدَّ (ʔasadda)","tags":["active","collective","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"place, position, post","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"سَدَّ مَسَدَّهُ","english":"to take someone's place"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"neck of a bottle (where the stopper is placed)","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ma.sad/","/ma.sa.da/","/mu.si.da/","/mas.sa.da/","/mus.din/","/mu.sidd/","/ma.sadd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38587","headword_ar":"مَسَدَ","root":"msd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masodN","text_ar":"مَسْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He twisted"},{"kind":"text","text":"a rope: (M, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he twisted it well."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masada","text_ar":"مَسَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masodN","text_ar":"مَسْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pursued a journey laboriously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with energy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he held on,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continued, the journey;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoA^aba Als~ayora","text_ar":"اَدْاَبَ السَّيْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he journeyed on continually, whether by night"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by day:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L:) because the so journeying renders an animal lean, or lank. (Lth, L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masada","text_ar":"مَسَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masodN","text_ar":"مَسْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(leguminous herbage, A, or continued travel, Lth)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered"},{"kind":"text","text":"an animal"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lean, lank, light of flesh, slender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lank in the belly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, A, L.) El-'Abdee says, describing a she-camel, and likening her to a wild bull,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yamosuduhu Alqaforu walayolN sadiY"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bare and waterless desert renders him lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dewy night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musida","text_ar":"مُسِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masodN","text_ar":"مَسْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the belly)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, soft, of small dimensions, even, and without any ugliness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L.) ―         -b5-  The following expression of Ru-beh,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yamosudu A^aEolaY laHomihi wayaA^orimuhu"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the milk of camels)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strengthens the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2716},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper parts of his flesh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(referring to a pastor, not to an ass, as J says, IB, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and renders it, firm."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasanapu Almasodi","text_ar":"حَسَنَةُ المَسْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a damsel, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mamosuwdapN","text_ar":"مَمْسُودَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (S, L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","L","K"]},{"entry_id":"n38588","headword_ar":"مَسَدٌ","root":"msd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fibres that grow at the roots of the branches of the palm-tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyfN","text_ar":"لِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, L:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabolN mino masadK","text_ar":"حَبْلٌ مِنْ مَسَدٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"halter, of those fibres:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A:) also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masadN","text_ar":"مَسَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rope of those fibres:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, L, K:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of those of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of palm-tree called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqol","text_ar":"مُقْل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Zj, L, K:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the leaves of the palm-tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the soft hair of the camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, L: [see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAhiqN","text_ar":"زَاهِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of other hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wool:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of hides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of camels' hides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of plants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bark of a tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of any thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plaited rope, firmly twisted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K,) of any of the materials above mentioned: (M, L:) applied to a rope, it is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mamosuwdN","text_ar":"مَمْسُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and is thus similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafoDN","text_ar":"نَفْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA nufiDa","text_ar":"ما نُفِضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amosaAdN","text_ar":"اَمْسَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misaAdN","text_ar":"مِسَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, L, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabolN mino masadK","text_ar":"حَبْلٌ مِنْ مَسَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur, cxi., last verse, is said to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A chain"},{"kind":"text","text":"seventy cubits in length, whereby the woman upon whose neck it is to be put shall be led into hell, (Zj, T, M, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firmly twisted of iron;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though it were"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rope of iron strongly twisted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masadN mugaArN","text_ar":"مَسَدٌ مُغَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A back compact like a rope strongly twisted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masadN","text_ar":"مَسَدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An iron axis of a pulley."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","L","M","K","Zj","T"]},{"entry_id":"n19297","headword_ar":"مَسَدٌّ","root":"sd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[properly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of closing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: see 1, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n19298","headword_ar":"مُسِدٌّ","root":"sd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadiydN","text_ar":"سَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}